[1] Czech Republic, wild boar, Zlinsky, update
Date: Wed 26 Jul 2017
Source: Official Czech Republic State Veterinary Administration web-site [in Czech, machine trans., summ. Com.SZ, edited]
https://www.svscr.cz/africky-mor-prasat-aktualni-informace/


African swine fever in the Czech Republic; Current information as of 26 Jul 2017
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The state veterinary administration tested 99 dead wild pigs found in the Zlín Region. Since yesterday [25 Jul 2017], 3 new confirmed cases have been added. In total, there are now 66. In all 3 new cases, the adults were found in the cadastral area of Klečuvka, where in the past weeks the infection has been confirmed in dead wild boar. In the remaining 33 cases, the test ended with a negative result.

In the area with intensive catches, 609 wild boars have been caught. Under the JRC Regulation all captured pigs in this area are investigated for ASF. No sample was positive yet, 607 samples tested negative and in 2 cases the examination could not be performed.

Today and tomorrow [26 and 27 Jul 2017) the training of hunters in the infested area will continue. So far, more than 350 hunters have been trained. The approval to catch the wild boar in the hunting area was granted by the Regional Veterinary Administration for the Zlín Region to 3 hunting associations.

